  - type discipline
abstract: "skillc is a static type-discipline compiler that verifies whether an agent skill's goal is achievable given a capability context and declared protocol. It fuses STRIPS capability-guarded reachability with multiparty session types over goal-marked global protocols, and is sound for refutation: an IMPOSSIBLE verdict is a proof that no run of the skill can reach its goal. The soundness core is mechanized in Coq with zero axioms."
documentation: "https://github.com/ginaecho/skill-achievability-compiler/blob/gc/implement-and-testing/README.md"
version: "1.0.0"
